{"/service/ndnp/nn/batch_nn_russell_ver01/data/sn83030193/17504467A/1908060901/0899.xml":{"full_text":"i a\nr rym wv A Ak 0 0 00 0 00 r 0 1ft\nilJ 1\n11 TilE EVENING WORLD TUESDAY JUNE 91908 11\nJ WOMANS ISLAND\nGARRISON DEFIES\nCITY WITH GUNS\nI\nI\nGuardians of Sunken Meadows\nI Declarc Truce to Test\nTitle in Court\nCLAIM ON OLD GRANT\nj Queen Anne Gave Island to\nthe Joneses but New York\nHolds Full House\nI\nThe five annex watchmen who have\nGuarded the ten acres In the East\nRiver between Randalls Island Ward\nIsland end Port MorrU known as tho\nSunken Meadows were descended upon\nby the police today and were taken to\nthe Harlem Court to tell whr they did\nnot permit the city to come Into Its\nawnThe\nThe Court soon heard from the law\nfirm of Finch Coleman of No 32\nNassau street that the city had bullet\nIn on the Sunken Meadows In the most\noutrageous fnohlcn The Island de\nclared the lawyers Is the property ol\nHIT Oliver Livingston Jones who Is\ndescended from tho Joneses of colonial\nAir and whose title to the Sunkor\nMeadows dates back to n patent granted\nto her ancestors by queen Anne\nCitys Full Home Title\nThe city claims title to the land by\ni some other process that goes back to\na tull house patent or In other\nwords a patent containing three kings\nand a pair of queen In the deal nut\nthe Jonoes hAve romalned In posses\nIon and as Blackstone or Coke or\nsome other venerably dead law Inter\npreter was pleased to remark posses\nsion is nine points of tho law\nLately Mrs Joness lawyers have\nfortified their possemlon with five\nwatchmen who for two years have\npatrolled the Inland night and day\nbearing arms shotguns and 45callbrc\nrevolvers with which to repel board\neTII Rlohard Mnhon has commanded\nthis little Barrison\nHe was In command yesterday when\nCity Surveyor James H Crowley two\nowlstont surveyors and two men from\nthe Dock Department snlle out and at\ntempted n landing on the Sunken tend\nOres Mahon met tho officials as they\nheaded in and permitted them to look\nInto the double bore of a shot n\nHe called out to thorn that they could\ntake their choice of remaining afloat\nor landing amid a shower of buckshot\nThey went hack to talk the thing over\nI with commissioners and deputy com\nmissioners Today they enlisted ilx\nII marine policemen of the Harbor Squad\nIn their fleet and sailed out to capture\nthe Island for the city\nGarrison Called a Truce\nMahon and his garrison came out\nwith their KIIIIS to meet the approach\ning naval demonstration There was a\nparley at the conclusion of which\nMahon consented to KO with three of\nhis men to court and test their rights\ntie left one man with a shotgun still\nmaintaining the posse ilon for Mrs\nOliver LlvlnKSt n Jones\nVhen Mrs Joness lawyers heard that\nfourfifths of the garrison had been kid\nnapped by the marine patrolmen and\nwere arraigned In the Harlem Court\nthey fcald things about the hlBhhandcl\nmethods of city oillcluls and promised\nII to Ret all sorts of writs and Injunctions\ni In bohnlf of their client\nThis U the most outrageous proceed\nInlt I ever heard of said Mr Coleman\nThe city knows that our title to the\nSunken Memlon is the best and tho\nDock Commissioner and the Corporation\nCounsel know thin we are In awful pos\nsession OtT and on for one hundred\njoarn the city has been claiming title to\nthe Island pmt It never had confidence\nenough In Its title to make an Issue of\nIt In court\nCity Once Paid Rent\nWhy ttlteen or twenty years ago\nthe city acknowledged our title by rent\ning a portion of tho Island from tu\nThe present aotlon Is taken probably\nbecause of a bill passed by the Legis\nlature recently In which the State\npassed to the city whatever title the\nstate had to tie Island The city Is\ngoing ahead now just as If that bill\ngave the city the Sunken Meadows\nwhereas the State had no more actual\ntitle to the Island than the city had\nWe will go after this thing In the\ncourts now prove our title 03 well\nem our possession\nMrs Oliver Livingston Jones Is ono\nof the richest women In the State and\nthe biggest landholder In Nassui\nCounty Long Island She was a Miss\nJones a descendant of ono of the oldest\nand most aristocratic families of New\nYork Her family were leaders of\nKnickerbocker society when the Van\nderblll foroV catching shad In\nStaten Island Sound\n91MMNBETTER\nJ EDWARD SIMMONS BETTER\nJ dward Simmons president of the\nFourth National Rank who has been\nill at his home No 38 West Klftyucc\noiid street for several days was said\nto bo very much Improved today Ills\nphysician said that Mr Simmons would\nbe out In a day or two\nI\nTROOPS FIGHT\nFIRE AT FORT\nI\nWADSWORTH\nCity Department Puts Out\nBlazeArson Attempted\nat Happyland\nFire routed several squads of United\nStated soldiers stationed at Fort Wads\nworth today and they were forced to\nsend In two alarms for reinforcements\nfrom the Staten Island Fire Depart\nment\nThe blare started In a detached\nbuilding near the ofllcers quarters\nThis building was occupied by the\nfamily of Sergt Fred Roberts on the\nfirst floor and that of Sergt James J\nParker on the second The fire started\nIn a closet In Siirgt Roberts apart I\nments and was burning merrily when I\none of the soldiers children told him I\nIt was getting pretty hot I\nThe Roberts and Parker families ran to\nthe open none too warmly clad and\nthen the cry of Flrel was sounded\nWhen lithe soldiers came from heir ja fo\ntack they formed brigades of some\nsort but not tire brigades Col Allen\nIn command of the fort sent In a cull fir\nlielp to the Fire Department Then\nwhen the house began blazing from\nfoundation to roof the Colonel cent In\na second call\nTho firemen came allot and the blaze\nwan oon whipped Uncle Sums loss\nwill be about 3MO\nPolice Capt Landon was making In\nquiries He wanted to know how the\ntire caught and wus questioning some\nsoldiers when a man came up to him\nand said\nIm John Weiss proprietor of Hap\npyland Park at South 